cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on lexical entailment. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a post-processing method to transform word vectors. Additionally, it could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of external linguistic constraints to improve the performance of a model. It may also be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with semantic similarity and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of neural networks.
